    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chairs designed for use at the beach, having a hood for protection from the sun and wind. May be made of wicker, wood and cloth, or other materials. Originally made of wicker in the 19th century, based on wicker armchair furniture with covered high rising hoods that had been created by basketmakers for centuries. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
